# Normalize line endings to LF on commit and on checkout.
#
# Rationale: the cross-platform parity tests in
# tests/test_cross_platform.py pin a SHA-256 of canonical JSON
# bytes. Mixed CRLF/LF in tracked files would risk silently
# breaking the byte-equality contract on a Windows clone with
# core.autocrlf=true. All currently tracked files already use
# LF (verified at the time this file was added), so this
# attribute makes the existing convention explicit and durable
# rather than introducing a new normalization step.
* text=auto eol=lf
